@startuml state-gate
' Tor-Lebenszyklus (GateController + Core-Enum GateState)
' Testkandidaten: G1 CanOpen_ReturnsFalse_WhenKeyMissing, G2 CanOpen_ReturnsTrue_WhenAllKeysPresent
skinparam state {
    BackgroundColor LightYellow
    BorderColor DarkGoldenRod
}

[*] --> Closed : Awake\n(GateLockData aus requiredKeyIds)

Closed --> Closed : OnTriggerEnter\n[kein Spieler\nODER requiredKeyIds leer\nODER CanOpen = false]
Closed --> Opening : OnTriggerEnter\n[Spieler & CanOpen = true]\n/ ConsumeKeys(requiredKeyIds)

note on link
    Verzweigung CanOpen prüft GateLockData.CanOpen(KeyInventory)
    Testkandidaten: G1 (Schlüssel fehlt), G2 (alle vorhanden)
end note

state Opening {
    note: OpenRoutine (Coroutine)\nSlerp doorPivot um openAngle\nüber openDuration
}

Opening --> Open : Rotation abgeschlossen

state Open {
    note: dauerhaft offen\nOnTriggerEnter ignoriert\n(State != Closed)
}

Open --> Open : OnTriggerEnter\n[State != Closed → Abbruch]
Open --> [*]

@enduml
